# moreComing

**Instance Property**

A Boolean value that indicates whether more results are available.

## Declaration

```swift
var moreComing: Bool { get }
```

## Discussion

If the server is unable to deliver all of the changed results with this operation object, it sets this property to [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/true] before executing the block in the [doc://com.apple.cloudkit/documentation/CloudKit/CKFetchRecordChangesOperation/fetchRecordChangesCompletionBlock] property. To fetch the remaining changes, create a new [doc://com.apple.cloudkit/documentation/CloudKit/CKFetchRecordChangesOperation] object using the change token that the server returns.

## Configuring the Fetch Record Changes Operation

- **recordZoneID**: The ID of the record zone with the records you want to fetch.
- **previousServerChangeToken**: The token that identifies the starting point for retrieving changes.
- **desiredKeys**: The fields to fetch for the requested records.
- **resultsLimit**: The maximum number of changed records to report with this operation object.
